<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>7781</id>
    <title>No confirmation fired when you exit a page in the middle of composing a message</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">When you re writing a Facebook message_ it s easy to accidentally leave the page_ and no browser alert is fired to make sure you intend to leave with your message partly written but unsent.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.2">I ve lost several long messages because of this (most recently due to browser error while choosing the photo to attach) and it s extremely annoying.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.3">Most other mail systems (Gmail_ Outlook_ etc.) confirm that you intend to abandon a message when you would exit_ and Facebook should do the same.</sentence>
            <sentence id="1.4">(Especially since all message writing is now done via a Javascript-based popup_ so even browsers that remember the message content like Firefox can t recover.)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">Thanks!</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
